## 2. Product Definition

Privyields is a private yield-product marketplace demo:

- Users prove they are qualified investors with ZK, without revealing exact assets.
- The app lists 10 mock yield products across treasury, real estate, staking, mining, credit, and DeFi strategies.
- Users choose a yield product and deposit ERC-7984 confidential cUSDC.
- Each product periodically publishes a public yield rate.
- The vault computes each user's product shares and rewards with FHE.
- Users decrypt only their own position and reward.

One-line pitch:

> ZK proves a user is qualified without revealing their wealth; ERC-7984 and FHE keep their yield allocations and rewards confidential.

## 3. Core User Flow

```text
ZK asset threshold proof
    |
    | prove assets >= 1,000,000 USDC without revealing exact assets
    v
Qualified user
    |
    | choose one of 10 listed yield products
    v
MockUSDC (ERC-20)
    |
    | approve + wrap
    v
ConfidentialUSDC (ERC-7984 wrapper)
    |
    | confidentialTransferAndCall(encryptedAmount, productId)
    v
ConfidentialYieldVault (IConfidentialFungibleTokenReceiver)
    |
    | encrypted allocations by product + encrypted rewards by product
    v
User decrypts own position/reward through Relayer SDK + ACL
```

## 4. Why This Product Works

The demo has three privacy layers with clear separation:

1. ZK eligibility
   - Proves the user has assets above a threshold.
   - Does not reveal the exact asset amount.
   - Used for qualified-investor access.

2. ERC-7984 confidential asset layer
   - Wraps public ERC-20 USDC into confidential cUSDC.
   - cUSDC balances and transfer amounts are encrypted handles.
   - `confidentialTransferAndCall` sends encrypted deposit amounts into the vault.

3. FHE yield accounting
   - Per-user product allocations are encrypted.
   - Per-user product rewards are encrypted.
   - Product yield rates are public.
   - Reward computation uses encrypted shares directly.

4. Vault custody model
   - User funds are held by `ConfidentialYieldVault`.
   - Yield products do not receive custody of funds in the MVP.
   - Products are public strategy labels plus yield-rate publishers.
   - The vault records encrypted allocations by `productId`.
   - The vault pays encrypted cUSDC rewards from its own reward liquidity.

Important honesty points:

- `wrap()` receives a public ERC-20 amount, so the wrap transaction itself is not confidential.
- The cUSDC balance and cUSDC-to-vault transfer amount are confidential after wrapping.
- Product selection is public in the MVP because `productId` is sent in callback data.
- The MVP is not anonymous and does not hide wallet addresses or timing.

